To push your local changes to GitHub, use the following sequence of commands:
1. git status to view any unsaved changes.
2. git add . to save all files or git add <dir/file> to save a specific file/folder.
3. git commit to commit files for saving. Use '-m' to include a message.
4. git push to push your changes to Github.

The following steps need to be taken to edit any class assignments posted in the class Github:
1. Navigate to your local version of the class repository.
2. Use git pull to "pull" any new files to your local version.
3. Use the scp command to copy new files to your personal repository.
4. Edit the files in your personal repository.
5. Add, commit, and push the files to your PERSONAL GitHub repository.
